    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offering a driver-focused 997.1 Carrera featuring the 3.6L flat-six M96.05 power plant. This unit is mechanically sorted, boasting a documented IMS bearing retrofit and a reinforced rear main seal. The six-speed manual transaxle provides precise gate entry, complemented by a factory-optioned limited-slip differential for superior corner-exit traction. The chassis retains its composure via Porsche Active Suspension Management (PASM) with refreshed bushings. While the exterior shows minor road-derived patina, the drivetrain remains thermally efficient with a low-temperature thermostat and upgraded radiators. A mechanically robust specimen optimized for immediate performance use.",
