    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 996.2 Carrera is a mechanically sound example of Porsche\u2019s water-cooled evolution. Powered by the 3.6L M96 flat-six, it delivers 320 hp through a G96 6-speed manual transaxle with a crisp, short-throw engagement. The engine features a documented dual-row IMS bearing retrofit and a recently replaced air-oil separator (AOS), mitigating common platform concerns. The suspension retains its factory composure with MacPherson struts up front and a multi-link rear setup, providing the communicative feedback and rear-biased weight transfer enthusiasts crave. Braking is handled by four-piston Brembo monobloc calipers over cross-drilled rotors, showing minimal swept-area wear. This is a driver-spec 911 with a focus on kinematic integrity and powertrain reliability.",
